title: 7 people shot in Antioch
content:
Seven people were injured in a shooting in Antioch, police said Sunday.
The victims, whose names weren't released, were shot on the 5500 block of Cedar Point Way about 11:50 p.m. Saturday, said Antioch police Sgt. Michael Hulsey.
Officers responding to reports of gunfire found five victims on the scene. Two more victims showed up at local hospitals, Hulsey said.
All the victims suffered wounds that were not life-threatening, police said.
No arrests have been made.
